(238, '2026 City of Grand Junction Energy and Lighting Project', '2026-03-14', 'CO', 'Supply and installation of lighting fixtures with retrofitting and replacement requirements', 'Lighting (Supply + Installation)', 55, 'Ikio Led Lighting LLC', 'GO', 'CHANGES SINCE LAST ANALYSIS\r\n- Added files (3): Addendum No. 2 2026 City of Grand Junction Energy and Lighting Project IFB-5809-26-DD.pdf, City of Grand Junction - Final.xlsx, Pre-Bid Sign In Sheet Energy and Lighting Project IFB-5809-26-DD.pdf\r\n- Modified files (1): City of Grand Junction, CO.pdf\r\n- Removed files (1): City of Grand Junction - QTY.xlsx\r\n\r\nSTEP 1 - RFP DATA EXTRACTION\r\n| **RFP Element**          | **Details**                                                                 |\r\n|--------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\n| Project Name             | 2026 City of Grand Junction Energy and Lighting Project                     |\r\n| RFP Number               | IFB-5809-26-DD                                                              |\r\n| Issuing Authority        | City of Grand Junction Purchasing Division                                  |\r\n| Submission Method        | Not specified                                                               |\r\n| Key Dates                | Addendum No. 1: February 3, 2026; Addendum No. 2: February 10, 2026         |\r\n| Contact                  | Dolly Daniels, Senior Buyer                                                 |\r\n\r\nEVALUATION SEQUENCE\r\n- **Supply**: Yes\r\n- **Installation**: Yes\r\n- **Substitution**: Not specified\r\n\r\nCOMPLIANCE TABLE\r\n- **Lighting Diffusers**: \"If the diffuser is broken prior to scope of work required, the City would request that the Contractor contact the Project Manager and an assessment will be made at that time.\"\r\n- **Flagpole Light**: \"Yes, the flagpole light is an LED, it does not need to be replaced at this time.\"\r\n- **Exterior Canopy Globe Lights**: \"Yes, use a 3000k type as-like bulb.\"\r\n\r\nFINAL RECOMMENDATION\r\nIkio Led Lighting LLC is recommended as the best company for the 2026 City of Grand Junction Energy and Lighting Project. Despite the lack of a state match (IN vs. CO), Ikio Led Lighting LLC is licensed in Colorado, which is a critical requirement. The company scored higher in licensing compliance compared to Ikio Energy, which is not licensed in the project state. Key risks include the absence of evidence for site visit capabilities, BABA/BAA/DB compliance, and specific qualifications. To mitigate these, it is recommended to schedule a pre-bid site visit and ensure compliance plans are in place. The next steps involve confirming local subcontractor partnerships and securing necessary bonds and insurance. **Executive Takeaway**: Ikio Led Lighting LLC, with its licensing advantage, is the most viable option, provided it addresses compliance and operational gaps.\r\n\r\nSCOPE OF WORK\r\nThe project involves the supply and installation of lighting fixtures at the Avalon Theatre and other locations, with specific requirements for retrofitting and replacing certain types of lights. Key requirements include compliance with BABA/BAA/DB standards, securing bonds and insurance, and conducting site visits to ensure proper installation and functionality.', '2026-02-16', '2026-02-16 07:16:19', 'submitted', 'won', 'IK-P/LTG/847092', '2026-02-01'),
(239, 'Boulder County Community Hub - Electrical', '2026-10-31', 'OR', 'Electrical installation and supply', 'Supply, installation, and substitution allowed', NULL, 'Ikio Led Lighting LLC', 'GO', 'CHANGES SINCE LAST ANALYSIS\r\n- Added files (1): Boulder Hub Lighting and Lighting Controls (Substitution).xlsx\r\n- Modified files (1): 4. Boulder County Bid Tabulation (Required with Submittal).xlsx\r\n\r\nSTEP 1 - RFP DATA EXTRACTION\r\n| **RFP Element**            | **Details**                                                                                                                                                                                                 |\r\n|----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\n| Project Name               | Boulder County Community Hub - Electrical                                                                                                                                                                   |\r\n| Submission Method          | Not specified                                                                                                                                                                                               |\r\n| Key Requirements           | Compliance with codes, laws, and ordinances; permits and governmental fees; shop drawings; coordination study; as-built drawings; lighting and lighting controls; insurance and bonding requirements.         |\r\n| Compliance Notes           | \"Materials and installation shall comply with codes, laws and ordinances of federal, state and local governing bodies having jurisdiction.\"                                                                 |\r\n\r\nEVALUATION SEQUENCE\r\n- **Supply**: Yes\r\n- **Installation**: Yes\r\n- **Substitution**: Allowed\r\n\r\nCOMPLIANCE TABLE\r\n- \"Materials and installation shall comply with codes, laws and ordinances of federal, state and local governing bodies having jurisdiction.\"\r\n\r\nFINAL RECOMMENDATION\r\nBased on the evaluation, Ikio Led Lighting LLC is recommended as the best company for the Boulder County Community Hub project. Despite the state mismatch, Ikio Led Lighting LLC is licensed in Oregon, which is crucial for compliance. The company scored higher in licensing and has a broader range of state licenses, which suggests a better capability to handle regulatory requirements. However, there are risks related to site visit capabilities, BABA/BAA/DB compliance, and bonding/insurance provisions. To mitigate these, it is recommended to engage local subcontractors for site visits and ensure compliance with federal requirements by sourcing compliant materials. The next steps include confirming the ability to meet insurance and bonding requirements and scheduling a pre-bid site visit. **Executive Takeaway**: Ikio Led Lighting LLC is the most suitable choice, but requires strategic partnerships and compliance checks to ensure project success.\r\n\r\nSCOPE OF WORK\r\n- **Work Type**: Electrical installation and supply\r\n- **Delivery Mode**: Supply, installation, and substitution allowed\r\n- **Key Requirements**: Compliance with local and federal codes, site visit, BABA/BAA/DB compliance, bonding, and insurance.', '2026-02-16', '2026-02-16 07:17:38', 'not started', NULL, 'IK-P/LTG/847093', '2026-02-17'),
(240, 'Campus Wide, LED Lighting PH2', '2026-04-11', 'SD', 'Supply and installation of LED lighting', 'Supply + Installation + Substitution Allowed', 55, 'Ikio Led Lighting LLC', 'GO', 'STEP 1 - RFP DATA EXTRACTION\r\n| **Field**                  | **Details**                                                                                                                                                                                                 |\r\n|----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\n| Project Name               | Campus Wide, LED Lighting PH2                                                                                                                                                                               |\r\n| Location                   | South Dakota State Fair, Huron, South Dakota                                                                                                                                                                |\r\n| OSE Number                 | M2326 --04X                                                                                                                                                                                                 |\r\n| Prepared By                | Bureau of Human Resources and Administration, Office of the State Engineer                                                                                                                                  |\r\n| State Engineer             | Stacy Watters, P.E.                                                                                                                                                                                         |\r\n| Substantial Completion Date| June 24, 2026                                                                                                                                                                                               |\r\n| Liquidated Damages         | $200.00 per calendar day after the Substantial Completion date                                                                                                                                              |\r\n| Bid Submission Deadline    | March 3, 2026, at 2:30 PM CT                                                                                                                                                                                |\r\n| Pre-Bid Meeting            | February 17, 2026, at 11:00 AM CT, Nordby Exhibit Hall Conference Room                                                                                                                                      |\r\n| Submission Method          | Electronically                                                                                                                                                                                              |\r\n| Quote/Citation             | \"Electronic bids will be accepted by the State Engineer on behalf of the South Dakota Department of Agriculture and Natural Resources at https://www.sd.gov/cs?id=sc_cat_item&sys_id=5fe94a441b3e7e50464487f5604bcb73\" |\r\n\r\nEVALUATION SEQUENCE\r\n- Supply: Yes\r\n- Installation: Yes\r\n- Substitution: Allowed\r\n\r\nCOMPLIANCE TABLE\r\n- **Liquidated Damages**: $200.00 per calendar day after the Substantial Completion date of June 24, 2026.\r\n- **Bid Bond Requirement**: Each bid in excess of $100,000.00 must include a 5% certified check or a 10% bid bond.\r\n- **Asbestos Statement**: No asbestos containing materials are to be installed in this project.\r\n\r\nFINAL RECOMMENDATION\r\nBased on the evaluation, Ikio Led Lighting LLC is recommended as the best company for the Campus Wide, LED Lighting PH2 project. Despite the company not being based in South Dakota, it is licensed to operate in the state, which is a critical requirement. However, the company needs to address several areas to ensure compliance and successful project execution. These include scheduling a pre-bid site visit, sourcing materials compliant with BABA/BAA/Davis Bacon requirements, and partnering with a certified local firm to meet SBE/MBE/WBE/HUB goals. Additionally, the company should confirm its bonding and insurance capabilities to meet project requirements. Key risks include potential delays in securing local partnerships and compliance materials, which can be mitigated by early engagement with local subcontractors and suppliers. The next steps involve confirming the ability to meet all project requirements and submitting a comprehensive bid package. Executive takeaway: Ikio Led Lighting LLC is well-positioned for this project with strategic adjustments.\r\n\r\nSCOPE OF WORK\r\n- **Work Type**: Supply and installation of LED lighting across the South Dakota State Fair campus.\r\n- **Delivery Mode**: Supply, installation, and substitution allowed.\r\n- **Key Requirements**: Mandatory site visit, compliance with BABA/BAA/Davis Bacon, provision of bonds and insurance.', '2026-02-16', '2026-02-16 07:18:10', 'submitted', 'won', 'IK-P/LTG/847094', '2026-02-16'),
(241, 'Canyons Softball Complex LED Sports Lighting', '2026-11-12', 'UT', 'Supply and installation of LED sports lighting with substitution allowed', 'Electronically', 55, 'Ikio Led Lighting LLC', 'GO', 'CHANGES SINCE LAST ANALYSIS\r\n- Added files (11): Canyons Softball Complex- Dynamo 4 Pro -Final.xlsx, Construction Schedule.pdf, Dynamo4_Pro_SFL_750W1000W1200W_5700K_HV_20D_TDS.pdf, GlareX_SFL_TDS.pdf, IKIO Submission.pdf, Ikio - St George Canyons Softball Complex bid bond.pdf, List of Subcontractor.pdf, St George Business License Certificate 8.4.2026.pdf, St. George Softball field lighting - #2.pdf, St. George Softball field lighting.pdf (+1 more)\r\n- Modified files (1): 1 - INFORMATION FOR BIDDERS .pdf\r\n- Removed files (2): Canyons Softball Complex Report.pdf, Dynamo4_Pro_SFL_750W1000W1200W_5000K_MV_30D_TDS.pdf\r\n\r\nSTEP 1 - RFP DATA EXTRACTION\r\n| **Field**                  | **Details**                                                                 |\r\n|----------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\n| Project Name               | Canyons Softball Complex LED Sports Lighting                                |\r\n| Project Address            | 1890 W 2000 N, St. George, UT 84770                                         |\r\n| Bid Opening Date           | January 26, 2026                                                            |\r\n| Pre-Bid Meeting Date       | February 2, 2026, 12 PM MST, Virtual                                        |\r\n| Questions Due Date         | February 10, 2026, 2 PM MST                                                 |\r\n| Submission Close Date      | February 12, 2026, 2 PM MST                                                 |\r\n| Submission Method          | Electronically                                                              |\r\n| Construction Start Date    | March 30, 2026                                                              |\r\n| Constructi