0k type as-like bulb.\"\n\nFINAL RECOMMENDATION\nIkio Led Lighting LLC is recommended as the best company for the 2026 City of Grand Junction Energy and Lighting Project. Despite the lack of a state match (IN vs. CO), Ikio Led Lighting LLC is licensed in Colorado, which is a critical requirement. The company scored higher in licensing compliance compared to Ikio Energy, which is not licensed in the project state. Key risks include the absence of evidence for site visit capabilities, BABA/BAA/DB compliance, and specific qualifications. To mitigate these, it is recommended to schedule a pre-bid site visit and ensure compliance plans are in place. The next steps involve confirming local subcontractor partnerships and securing necessary bonds and insurance. **Executive Takeaway**: Ikio Led Lighting LLC, with its licensing advantage, is the most viable option, provided it addresses compliance and operational gaps.\n\nSCOPE OF WORK\nThe project involves the supply and installation of lighting fixtures at the Avalon Theatre and other locations, with specific requirements for retrofitting and replacing certain types of lights. Key requirements include compliance with BABA/BAA/DB standards, securing bonds and insurance, and conducting site visits to ensure proper installation and functionality.', 'no_go_decision', '2026-02-16 07:16:19'),
(239, 239, 'Boulder County Community Hub - Electrical', '2025-10-31', 'OR', 'Electrical installation and supply', 'Supply, installation, and substitution allowed', NULL, 'Ikio Led Lighting LLC', 'No-Go', 'CHANGES SINCE LAST ANALYSIS\n- Added files (1): Boulder Hub Lighting and Lighting Controls (Substitution).xlsx\n- Modified files (1): 4. Boulder County Bid Tabulation (Required with Submittal).xlsx\n\nSTEP 1 - RFP DATA EXTRACTION\n| **RFP Element**            | **Details**                                                                                                                                                                                                 |\n|----------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| Project Name               | Boulder County Community Hub - Electrical                                                                                                                                                                   |\n| Submission Method          | Not specified                                                                                                                                                                                               |\n| Key Requirements           | Compliance with codes, laws, and ordinances; permits and governmental fees; shop drawings; coordination study; as-built drawings; lighting and lighting controls; insurance and bonding requirements.         |\n| Compliance Notes           | \"Materials and installation shall comply with codes, laws and ordinances of federal, state and local governing bodies having jurisdiction.\"                                                                 |\n\nEVALUATION SEQUENCE\n- **Supply**: Yes\n- **Installation**: Yes\n- **Substitution**: Allowed\n\nCOMPLIANCE TABLE\n- \"Materials an